    <PrimAttribute name="comment" id="0a1bd98c-3d39-44c7-98b3-e95df7eff621">
        <type name="String"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="id" id="a3f24d0e-7b78-4edb-a51b-a7ed7d9a5f5c">
        <length>14</length>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="String"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>

########################

The ID is 13 in length, but should be limited to 6 for actual data input.

This is because all terminal areas  automatically have a SWAP stack created for them,  this swap stack has the same ID as the area with a 'SWAP_' prefix.

If the terminal area is a type that requires a transfer area, like a rail area, the system also creates a transfer area automatically. The transfer area's ID is the area ID with a 'TA' suffix. 
This transfer area also has a swap stack which will basically have an ID that is 'SWAP_' + ID + 'TA'.

e.g.

Rail Area ID - 'RAILGO', this has a swap stack called 'SWAP_RAILGO', a transfer area called 'RAILGOTA' which in turn has a swap stack of 'SWAP_RAILGOTA'.

** AN Exception to this rule is Yard Interchange areas. They do not have swap areas and are now limited to 8 characters in length.

Easy Eh!</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
